+# ADR 0006 ‚Äî Stabilization: home-route link uses next/link, add a navigation guard test
+
+Status: Accepted
+Date: 2026-05-28
+Seed: sdlc2/ai-bookkeeper-cert-3
+Supersedes/relates: stabilization debt carried by cert-1 (shipped via scope-creep) and cert-2 (held formatMoney's release on it)
+
+## Context
+The stabilization seed reports a Next.js lint regression in `src/app/page.tsx`: a raw
+`<a href="/">` element flagged by `@next/next/no-html-link-for-pages`, blocking release for two cycles.
+
+Empirical finding (inspected the committed tree, not the seed's description):
+- `src/app/page.tsx:12` ‚Äî the home/brand link is ALREADY `<Link href="/">` (next/link). `next/link` is imported (`page.tsx:2`).
+- Every internal page route on the page already uses `<Link>`: `/` (l.12), `/pricing` (l.35,119,366,429), `/faq` (l.38,435), `/dashboard` (l.41,409,441).
+- The only raw `<a>` tags target in-page hash anchors (`#how`, `#start` ‚Äî l.31,45,106,401), which `no-html-link-for-pages` does NOT flag.
+- `eslint .` exits 0 (GREEN). The functional `<a>`‚Üí`<Link>` conversion the seed asks for is already present ‚Äî it is a no-op.
+
