+# Release v0.5.0 ‚Äî Money Display Formatter + Phase 2/3 Showcase
+
+**Date:** 2026-05-29
+**Bump:** MINOR (`0.4.0 ‚Üí 0.5.0`)
+**Tag:** `v0.5.0` ‚Üí release commit
+
+## Why this version
+
+Backward-compatible feature additions, **no breaking changes** since `0.4.0`.
+Under `0.x` semantic versioning a feature release increments the **minor**, so
+this lands as `0.5.0`. The bump is derived from the merged history, not guessed:
+`git log v0.4.0..HEAD` is three `feat` commits (formatMoney ADR 0004; Phase 2
+polish; Phase 3 showcase) plus one `test` (e2e home-nav guard) and one `docs`
+(README) ‚Äî all additive, none breaking.
+
+## Headline
+
+The money layer is now complete end-to-end: `formatMoney` (ADR 0004) is the
+display-side counterpart to `roundMoney` (ADR 0002) and `addMoney`/`subtractMoney`
+(ADR 0003), so what the user sees can never drift from what the ledger stores.
+Around it ships the Phase 2/3 product showcase ‚Äî an interactive ledger demo,
+motion choreography, pricing + FAQ pages, ink-mode toggle, and a11y polish.
+
+## What's new
+
+- **Currency-aware money display formatter** (`formatMoney`, ADR 0004).
+  `formatMoney(value, currency, locale?)` normalizes through `roundMoney` first,
+  then delegates symbol/grouping/minor-unit precision to `Intl.NumberFormat`
+  (JPY‚Üí0, USD‚Üí2, BHD‚Üí3; `locale` defaults to `"en-US"`). Fail-loud: non-finite
+  or mixed-currency throws `MoneyArithmeticError`; blank/unknown currency throws
+  `RangeError`. `formatMoney(addMoney(0.1, 0.2, "USD"), "USD")` is exactly
+  `"$0.30"`. Pure, side-effect-free. 8 new unit tests (suite 42/42 green).
+- **Phase 3 showcase.** Interactive double-entry ledger demo, Framer Motion
+  choreography (`src/lib/motion.ts`), pricing + FAQ pages, ink-mode toggle, a11y
+  polish. UI-only; no API or behavior change.
+- **Phase 2 polish.** Regenerated hero background, OG share card, PWA manifest +
+  icon set. Presentation/assets only.
+- **Home-nav e2e regression guard** (ADR 0006). Playwright guard locking in the
+  `next/link` home navigation, preventing regression of the raw-anchor lint
+  defect that previously held this release.
+
+## Bump rationale (auditable)
+
+| Input | Signal | Bump |
+|-------|--------|------|
+| `feat(ledger): formatMoney (ADR 0004)` (`12bc223`) | new backward-compatible API | MINOR |
+| `feat: phase 3 showcase` (`ac478e9`) | UI/feature, no API change | MINOR-equiv |
+| `feat: phase 2 polish` (`b444125`) | assets/presentation | PATCH-equiv |
+| `test(e2e): home-nav guard (ADR 0006)` (`b510ec9`) | test only | ‚Äî |
+| `docs: rewrite README` (`cf108a7`) | docs only | ‚Äî |
+| Breaking changes since `v0.4.0`? | none | ‚Äî |
+
+‚Üí Highest applicable bump = **MINOR** ‚Üí `0.5.0`.
+
+## Release-quality gate (cleared)
+
+The `v0.5.0` release was previously **held** at `12bc223`: a red ESLint error
+(`@next/next/no-html-link-for-pages` ‚Äî a raw `<a href="/">` in
+`src/app/page.tsx`, introduced inside `v0.4.0`'s visual v2 work) failed the
+trunk-quality bar. That defect is now **fixed** ‚Äî `page.tsx` uses `next/link`,
+and ADR 0006 added a Playwright guard against its regression. The full gate is
+green on this release:
+
+- `eslint .` ‚Äî **clean** (0 errors, 0 warnings)
+- `tsc --noEmit` ‚Äî **clean**
+- `tsx --test` ‚Äî **42/42 pass**
+- `next build` ‚Äî **success** (8 static routes prerendered)
+
+All four green ‚Üí tag cut.
+
+## Known issues / carried-over follow-ups
+
+- **`postcss` XSS still open (partial fix)** ‚Äî GHSA-qx2v-qp2m-jg93 (moderate).
+  Top-level `postcss` is pinned `^8.5.15`, but `next@16.2.6` nests
